An official of the Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation (NNPC), Mrs. Yemi Awolola, who was arrested last week for alleged child-torture in Kaduna, has been remanded in a correctional facility. Mrs Awolola, who is standing trial before Chief Magistrate Bashir Shitu Yusuf at a Senior Magistrate Court 3, was arrested on July 6 for allegedly burning the genitals of a 14-year-old house help with a hot object. Immediate past chair of International Federation of Female Lawyers (FIDA), Bukola Ajao, said the suspect has pleaded guilty to the charge. Wife of the state governor, Hajiya Ummi El-Rufai, witnessed the court proceedings. The case was adjourned till August 27.